               <p>CEPHAS COX. I am a <rs id="t18280911-387-viclabel2016" type="occupation">bookseller</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18280911-387-victim2084 t18280911-387-viclabel2016"></join> and live in <placeName id="t18280911-387-crimeloc2017">Gray'sinn-road</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18280911-387-crimeloc2017" type="placeName" value="Gray'sinn-road"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18280911-387-crimeloc2017" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18280911-387-off2014 t18280911-387-crimeloc2017"></join>. I lost four books from a box at the side of my door about two o'clock in the afternoon on the 24th of July; I saw the prisoner take them and run away; I went after him and saw him stopped by another person.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18280911-387-person2085">
                  JAMES 
                  GOLDSMITH
               <interp inst="t18280911-387-person2085" type="surname" value="GOLDSMITH"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280911-387-person2085" type="given" value="JAMES"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280911-387-person2085" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I heard a cry, Stop thief! I looked out and saw the prisoner; he threw down these books at the corner of a street; a man took them up and gave them to me; I looked at them till the prisoner was brought back, and then I gave them up.(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18280911-387-person2086">
                  SAMUEL 
                  MOUNTSTEPHENS
               <interp inst="t18280911-387-person2086" type="surname" value="MOUNTSTEPHENS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280911-387-person2086" type="given" value="SAMUEL"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18280911-387-person2086" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am an officer. The prisoner was given to me; I took him to the office; he said it was the first time he had ever been guilty of such an act, and he hoped the prosecutor would forgive him.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. Another young man and I were walking down Gray's Inn-lane, and he wanted to go home to dinner; I said if he would stop I would pay for his dinner; he ran away and I after him; I suppose some other person took the books.</p>
